<emphasis id="B97AA719857B1441E660FE16FE4B06CA" box="[305,405,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="362">M. astra</emphasis>
(Last, Manjaji-Matsumoto &amp; Pogonoski, 2008)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E0088857B1441E486FE16FADF06CB" authority="Gray, 1851" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1851" box="[983,1281,404,429]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Trygon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="362" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gerrardi">
<emphasis id="B97AA719857B1441E486FE16FB8106CB" box="[983,1119,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="362">M. gerrardi</emphasis>
(Gray, 1851)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E0088857B1441E240FE16FE9506B6" authority="Bleeker, 1852" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1852" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Maculabatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="362" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrura">
<emphasis id="B97AA719857B1441E240FE16FA4206CA" box="[1297,1436,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="362">M. macrura</emphasis>
(Bleeker, 1852)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E0088857B1441E60BFE3AFD0206B6" authority="Bleeker, 1852" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1852" box="[346,732,439,464]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Maculabatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="362" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pastinacoides">
<emphasis id="B97AA719857B1441E60BFE3AFDC306B6" box="[346,541,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="362">M. pastinacoides</emphasis>
(Bleeker, 1852)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E0088857B1441E5BAFE3AFAB106B6" authority="Last, Manjaji-Matsumoto &amp; Moore, 2012" authorityName="Last, Manjaji-Matsumoto &amp; Moore" authorityYear="2012" box="[747,1391,439,464]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Maculabatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="362" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="randalli">
<emphasis id="B97AA719857B1441E5BAFE3AFCB006B6" box="[747,878,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="362">M. randalli</emphasis>
(Last, Manjaji-Matsumoto &amp; Moore, 2012)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E0088857B1441E22CFE3AFE5B0692" authority="Whitley, 1939" authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1939" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Maculabatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="362" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="toshi">
<emphasis id="B97AA719857B1441E22CFE3AFF100693" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="362">M. toshi</emphasis>
(Whitley, 1939)
</taxonomicName>
and three undescribed species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3142880857B1441E796FD83FD7A05CE" pageId="17" pageNumber="362" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB17B0B857B1441E796FD83FD7A05CE" blockId="17.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="17" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis id="B97AA719857B1441E796FD83FEEA057E" bold="true" box="[199,308,512,536]" pageId="17" pageNumber="362">Remarks</emphasis>
. Newly erected, morphologically similar genus consisting of nine medium to large, marine whiprays previously placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E0088857B1441E62EFDA6FE24055A" box="[383,506,549,572]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Himantura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="362" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AA719857B1441E62EFDA6FE24055A" box="[383,506,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="362">Himantura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The group contains at least three new species that are presently being described by the authors and their associates. Molecular analyses have divided the group into two subgroups; one containing largely black-spotted and/or white-spotted whiprays (gerrardi-complex), and another of largely plain-coloured whiprays (pastinacoides-complex) (see 
<figureCitation id="1335678E857B1441E502FD0CFD4805CE" box="[595,662,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1873,1895]" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dasyatidae (subfamily Urogymninae). Topology and branch lengths resulting from a constrained Maximum" pageId="17" pageNumber="362">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
